---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Types of SSDI Claims | ssdicalc.com';
const description = 'Types of conditions that qualify for SSDI: physical, mental, and neurological impairments.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Types of SSDI Claims</h1>

  <h2>Musculoskeletal Disorders</h2>
  <p>Back disorders, arthritis, degenerative disc disease, and joint problems are the most common basis for SSDI claims. You must show the condition prevents all substantial gainful work, not just your past job.</p>

  <h2>Cardiovascular Conditions</h2>
  <p>Heart failure, coronary artery disease, and chronic heart conditions. SSA's Blue Book listing 4.00 covers cardiovascular impairments and includes specific clinical criteria.</p>

  <h2>Mental Health Conditions</h2>
  <p>Depression, anxiety disorders, PTSD, bipolar disorder, and schizophrenia. Mental health claims require documented treatment history and evidence of functional limitations in areas like concentration, social interaction, and task persistence.</p>

  <h2>Neurological Conditions</h2>
  <p>Epilepsy, multiple sclerosis, Parkinson's disease, and traumatic brain injury. SSA's Blue Book listings 11.00 cover neurological impairments.</p>

  <h2>Cancer</h2>
  <p>Many cancers meet SSA's Compassionate Allowances program criteria for expedited decisions — sometimes approved within weeks.</p>

  <h2>Chronic Respiratory Conditions</h2>
  <p>COPD, asthma, and pulmonary fibrosis. Objective pulmonary function test results are critical to establishing eligibility.</p>

  <h2>Chronic Pain and Fatigue</h2>
  <p>Fibromyalgia and chronic fatigue syndrome are recognized impairments. Claimants must document consistent treatment and functional limitations with medical evidence.</p>
</BaseLayout>
